## **ğŸ“Œ 6. Troubleshooting in CloudOps Deployment**  
Troubleshooting is **critical** to ensure deployments run smoothly without issues.  

### **ğŸ’¡ Key Points:**  
âœ… **Deployment Failures:**  
   ğŸ”¹ Check **CloudFormation stack errors**.  
   ğŸ”¹ Debug **AWS CodeDeploy logs** for rollback issues.  
   ğŸ”¹ Verify IAM permissions for deployment automation.  

âœ… **Performance Issues:**  
   ğŸ”¹ Use **CloudWatch Metrics & Alarms** to monitor EC2, RDS, and Lambda performance.  
   ğŸ”¹ Identify network issues with **AWS VPC Flow Logs**.  

âœ… **Security & Compliance Issues:**  
   ğŸ”¹ Use **AWS Config & GuardDuty** to check for misconfigurations.  
   ğŸ”¹ Review **CloudTrail logs** for unauthorized access attempts.  

- **Hands-on:**  
  ğŸ”¹ Debug a **failed CloudFormation stack deployment**.  
  ğŸ”¹ Use **AWS Systems Manager Session Manager** to troubleshoot an EC2 instance.  

